South African President Cyril Ramaphosa. Rodger Bosch / AFP JOHANNESBURG - The National Joint Operational and Intelligence Structure say it has put measures in place to ensure safety and security during the State of the Nation Address. According to the structure, security forces have been deployed and are on high alert to ensure that SONA takes place in a secure environment. READ: SONA 2022 | DA calls for action plan and implementation It's warned that any action aimed at disrupting SONA or intentionally contravening the law, will be dealt with. Cape Town residents in the vicinity of City Hall are advised to check road closures ahead of the address.